# Backup files and directories - CRITICAL SECURITY
backups/
*backup*/
*.sql
# Track every numbered Drizzle migration from 0010 onwards. The
# historical Drizzle-generated SQL files (0000–0009, plus the ad-hoc
# `fix_submission_vendors_schema.sql`) are intentionally NOT tracked:
# production has historically been kept in sync via `drizzle-kit push`,
# and re-introducing them as executable numbered files would make them
# "pending" on environments whose `schema_migrations` was baselined
# without them, where they would fail (they are not idempotent — raw
# `CREATE TYPE` / `CREATE TABLE`).
#
# The wildcard negation is placed AFTER the `*.sql` rule so gitignore
# precedence (last matching rule wins) keeps numbered migrations
# trackable. The five `migrations/000N_*.sql` re-ignores below claw
# back the historical 0000–0009 files so only 0010+ are tracked.
# IMPORTANT: when adding a new numbered migration (e.g. 0015_*.sql),
# nothing else needs to change here — the wildcard already tracks it.
# This wildcard fix landed after a deploy outage caused by the prior
# rule ignoring every migration except 0010.
!migrations/[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]_*.sql
migrations/0000_*.sql
migrations/0001_*.sql
migrations/0002_*.sql
migrations/0003_*.sql
migrations/0004_*.sql
migrations/0005_*.sql
migrations/0006_*.sql
migrations/0007_*.sql
migrations/0008_*.sql
migrations/0009_*.sql
*.dump
*.bak
*_backup_*
uploads_backup_*
uploads/

